{"headline": "Taking Questions on How to Negotiate Family Conflict", "body": "\nOur new Ask an Expert features  \n, an expert in the field of conflict negotiation, who will answer reader questions about how to resolve disputes in families and businesses: from who is hosting the holiday party to how to tell your employees there is no year-end bonus. It\u2019s a month for difficult conversations.         \n\nMs. Heen is a founding partner at Triad Consulting Group and a lecturer on law at Harvard Law School. For the past 20 years she has helped develop negotiation theory and practice at the Harvard Negotiation Project. She teaches a class in negotiation at Harvard Law School and Advanced Negotiation through the Harvard Negotiation Institute.         \n\nShe wrote \u201c \n\u201d (Penguin, 2000), with Douglas Stone and  \n. Ms. Heen and Mr. Stone have a book coming out in March called \u201c \n: The Science and Art of Receiving Feedback Well (Even When It\u2019s Off Base, Unfair, Poorly Delivered, and Frankly, You\u2019re Not in the Mood)\u201d (Viking, 2014).         \n\nIn her practice at Triad, Ms. Heen has consulted on topics as varied as Greek and Turkish Cypriot relations and families debating the merits of organ donation. Her specialty is navigating emotionally charged negotiations. She says she \u201chelps people know how to approach difficult conversations with more skill and less anxiety.\u201d         \n\nHere are examples of some questions that Ms. Heen is prepared to answer:         \n\n1. How do I talk to my adult daughters about their children destroying things when they stay at our house?         \n\n2. My parents are too old to host a party, but they insist that we all come over, stay over and have an enormous formal meal with three generations and chaos. They can barely stand, but have iron wills. How can we opt out?         \n\n3. How do I tell my spouse that I didn\u2019t get the bonus we expected (knowing that the money is already spent)?         \n\n \n        ", "url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/02/booming/taking-questions-on-how-to-negotiate-family-conflict.html", "date": "2013-12-02", "description": "Sheila Heen, an expert in the field of conflict negotiation, will answer questions about how to approach difficult conversations and situations."}